---
id: org.dxos.plugin.thread
name: ThreadPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

ThreadPlugin renders comment threads anchored to ECHO objects (primarily Markdown documents). This spec covers the **comment-thread AI agent** feature: per-thread opt-in AI that responds to user comments either automatically or on @mention, with a model-selected response shape (reply message or document edit proposal).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## Types

```mdl
type AgentMode
  literals: auto | mention
  desc: Per-thread agent firing policy.
```

```mdl
type AgentConfig
  desc: Per-thread agent configuration. Stored on Thread.Thread as optional field.
  fields:
    enabled: Boolean
    mode: AgentMode
```

```mdl
type Thread
  desc: |
    Extends the existing org.dxos.type.thread schema. Version bumps to 0.2.0.
    The `agent` field is optional; absent or disabled means no AI involvement.
  fields:
    agent?: AgentConfig
```

```mdl
type AgentIdentity
  desc: |
    Effect Context.Tag. Resolved at runtime, not stored on threads.
    Default layer reads from the plugin Settings (`agentName`); tests/stories
    provide static layers; the host may layer in a workspace-scoped producer.
  fields:
    name: String          # display name + @mention token
    identityDid?: String  # optional ECHO identity DID stamped on assistant messages
    avatar?: String       # optional icon hint
```

## Services

```mdl
service AgentRunner
  desc: |
    Capability that executes one agent turn for a given thread + subject.
    Default implementation performs one `LanguageModel.generateText` call
    with edit tools (`editAnchoredRange`, `updateDocument`) registered per
    turn. Stub implementations are used in storybook + tests.
  methods:
    run(thread: Thread, subject: Obj.Any) -> Effect<void>
```

## Operations

```mdl
op RespondToThread
  key: org.dxos.plugin.thread.operation.respond-to-thread
  desc: Run one agent turn against a thread. Scheduled by AddMessage when the gate passes.
  input:
    thread: Ref<Thread>
    subject: Ref<Obj.Any>

op SetAgentConfig
  key: org.dxos.plugin.thread.operation.set-agent-config
  desc: Mutate thread.agent. Undefined config means off.
  input:
    thread: Ref<Thread>
    config?: AgentConfig
```

## Components

```mdl
component AgentToggle
  desc: |
    Per-thread radio popover hung off the thread header in CommentsPanel.
    Three states: off / mention / auto. Shows the resolved AgentIdentity.name
    as a read-only label.
  props:
    value?: AgentConfig
    agentName: String
  emits:
    change: { config?: AgentConfig }
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────┐
    │ Agent: {agentName}           │
    │                              │
    │  ◯ Off                       │
    │  ◉ Reply only on @mention    │
    │  ◯ Auto-respond              │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Per-thread agent configuration

  req F-1.1: Thread schema MUST add an optional `agent: AgentConfig` field
    without breaking existing threads (no migration required).

  req F-1.2: The `AgentIdentity` Effect service MUST be the sole source of
    the agent's display name. Thread schema MUST NOT store the name.

  req F-1.3: ThreadPlugin MUST contribute a default `AgentIdentity` capability
    at plugin activation (`{ name: 'Kai' }`). Hosts overriding the default
    contribute their own `AgentIdentity` earlier in plugin order so
    `Capability.get` returns it first.

feat F-2: Trigger gate

  req F-2.1: ThreadOperation.AddMessage MUST evaluate the gate after appending
    the message and MUST schedule (not invoke) RespondToThread when it passes.

  req F-2.2: The gate MUST return true iff ALL hold:
    - thread.agent?.enabled === true
    - message.sender.role !== 'assistant'  # user-authored messages carry no role
    - thread.status !== 'resolved'
    - mode === 'auto' OR text contains '@' + agentName (case-insensitive)

  req F-2.3: The gate MUST NOT fire on assistant messages (self-loop guard).

  req F-2.4: Flipping enabled on a thread MUST NOT retroactively respond to
    prior messages; only future user messages.

feat F-3: Agent runner

  req F-3.1: The runner MUST be a Capability so storybook and tests can swap
    in a stub without changing call sites.

  req F-3.2: The default runner MUST execute one LLM turn via
    `LanguageModel.generateText`, providing the thread message history as
    prompt and appending the response (or a synthesized post-tool ack) as
    an assistant message on the same thread.

  req F-3.3: The agent MUST be given edit tools for in-place markdown updates:
    - `editAnchoredRange(replacement)` — splices the replacement into the
      anchored span via Automerge-diff (`updateText`) and rewrites the
      AnchoredTo cursor so the comment marker tracks the new text.
    - `updateDocument(content)` — replaces the entire document content.

  req F-3.4: When the subject is not a Markdown.Document (no editable text in
    scope), the runner MUST omit the edit tools and only post a chat reply.

  req F-3.5: Assistant messages emitted by the runner MUST carry
    sender = { role: 'assistant', name: identity.name, identityDid: identity.identityDid }.

  req F-3.6: Runner errors MUST be caught at the operation handler boundary,
    logged via @dxos/log, and emit a `threads.agent.failed` observability event.
    The user's message MUST remain in the thread.

feat F-4: Toggle UI

  req F-4.1: CommentsPanel MUST render an AgentToggle icon button per thread,
    next to existing controls (resolve, delete).

  req F-4.2: Clicking the toggle MUST open a popover with three radio options
    (off / mention / auto) and a non-editable label showing AgentIdentity.name.

  req F-4.3: Changes MUST go through ThreadOperation.SetAgentConfig, not
    direct schema writes from the popover.

  req F-4.4: No UI is provided for changing the agent name in v1; the name
    is read-only from the user's perspective.

feat F-5: Storybook coverage

  req F-5.1: CommentsCompanion.stories.tsx MUST add three new variants:
    - `WithMentionAgent`: thread auto-opted-in with mode='mention'; stub runner.
    - `WithAutoAgent`: thread auto-opted-in with mode='auto'; stub runner.
    - `WithLiveAgent`: thread auto-opted-in with mode='auto'; live runner
      (Anthropic via DXOS edge).

  req F-5.2: `WithMentionAgent` and `WithAutoAgent` MUST contribute a stub
    `AgentRunner` that performs a canned `postReply` and never makes network
    calls (so headless `test-storybook` runs are deterministic and offline).

  req F-5.3: `WithLiveAgent` MUST contribute an `AppCapabilities.AiServiceLayer`
    (Anthropic via DXOS edge) so ThreadPlugin's default LLM-backed `AgentRunner`
    reaches a real model. Headless `test-storybook` renders but does not submit
    a comment, so no network call occurs in CI.

  req F-5.4: All three variants MUST contribute a static `AgentIdentity`
    capability (e.g. `{ name: 'Kai' }`) so the runner stamps the assistant
    message correctly even when no host layer is present.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Auto mode responds to every user message
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'auto' }
  when: A user appends a text message via ThreadOperation.AddMessage
  then:
    - RespondToThread is scheduled exactly once
    - The runner's `run` is invoked with the thread and subject

test T-2: Mention mode gates on @name
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'mention' }, identity.name = 'claude'
  when: A user posts "hello world" (no mention) then "hey @Claude check this"
  then:
    - The first message does not schedule RespondToThread
    - The second message schedules RespondToThread

test T-3: Self-loop guard
  given: A thread with agent = { enabled: true, mode: 'auto' }
  when: A message with sender.role = 'assistant' is appended
  then: RespondToThread is NOT scheduled

test T-4: Resolved threads do not trigger
  given: A thread with agent.enabled = true and status = 'resolved'
  when: A user appends a message
  then: RespondToThread is NOT scheduled

test T-5: Disabled mid-conversation does not delete history
  given: A thread with prior assistant messages
  when: SetAgentConfig is invoked with config = undefined
  then:
    - thread.agent becomes undefined
    - thread.messages is unchanged

test T-6: Story WithAutoAgent posts an assistant reply
  given: The WithAutoAgent storybook variant is rendered
  when: The user types "hello" and clicks send
  then:
    - The thread shows two messages
    - The second message has sender.role = 'assistant' and sender.name = 'echo'

test T-7: Story WithMentionAgent gates correctly
  given: The WithMentionAgent storybook variant is rendered
  when: The user posts "hello" then "@echo hello"
  then:
    - After the first send, only the user message is visible
    - After the second send, an assistant message is appended

test T-8: Runner errors do not lose the user message
  given: A thread with agent enabled and a runner stubbed to fail
  when: A user appends a message
  then:
    - The user message persists in the thread
    - A `threads.agent.failed` observability event is emitted
    - No assistant message is appended
```

## Out of Scope (v1)

- Per-document default agent config (was discussed during brainstorming; punted).
- UI to rename the agent within Composer (lives in plugin settings).
- "Thinking…" / streaming indicator on the message list.
- Cancellation of in-flight runner turns when the agent is disabled mid-turn.
- De-duplication of concurrent triggers from multiple users on the same thread.
- Token-budget caps on long threads or large documents.
